What is SQL?
SQL (Structured Query Language) is used to communicate with a database.
It helps us store, retrieve, update, and delete data.

What is SELECT?

The SELECT statement is used to retrieve data from a table in a database.
It is the most basic and most commonly used SQL command.

Syntax
SELECT column_name
FROM table_name;

| id | name | salary |
| -- | ---- | ------ |
| 1  | Ravi | 50000  |
| 2  | Neha | 60000  |
| 3  | Aman | 55000  |

Example 1: Select all columns
SELECT *
FROM employees;
Explanation:
* means all columns.
This query will display all records from the employees table.


Example 2: Select specific columns
SELECT name, salary
FROM employees;
Explanation:
This query shows only the name and salary columns from the table.
Output:
| name | salary |
| ---- | ------ |
| Ravi | 50000  |
| Neha | 60000  |
| Aman | 55000  |
